  "prompt": "What is the best way to get my money back from an internet scam?",
  "response": "If you've fallen victim to an internet scam, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Contact your bank or credit card company immediately to report the fraud and potentially stop or reverse charges.\n\n2. File a report with local law enforcement.\n\n3. Report the scam to the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) at ReportFraud.ftc.gov.\n\n4. If it was an online purchase, contact the website or platform where the transaction occurred.\n\n5. Check if your credit card offers fraud protection.\n\n6. Monitor your accounts for any additional suspicious activity.\n\nHowever, recovering money from internet scams can be difficult, and there's no guarantee you'll get all or any of your money back. Prevention is always the best approach.",
